<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-185-936  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 185 936.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  Jan 1 1990 v29 n1 p77(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CAD/CASE tool integrators face several hurdles. (computer-aideddesign and computer-aided software engineering)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wasserman, Anthony I.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The CAD Framework Initiative is intended to define an overallframework for integrating computer-aided design and computer-aidedsoftware engineering tools to provide a way to link the two intointegrated systems.andP;  The four kinds of CAD and CASE integrationthat must be addressed are platform integration, presentationintegration, data integration and control integration.andP;  The CADand CASE tools should work together in a distributed environmentand should share a common look and feel; window-based interfacessuch as DECwindows and the Open Software Foundation's Motif willlikely be included in the integrated tool sets.andP;  InteractiveDevelopment Environments' Software through Pictures is anintegrated CASE environment that uses a shared repository for dataaccessible by various tools; also described are IBM's AD/Cycle andAtherton Technology's Software Backplane.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Program Development ToolsComputer-Aided Software EngineeringComputer-Aided DesignIntegrated SystemsSystem DesignNew TechniqueInteroperability.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>